<!-- ##### SECTION Title ##### -->
GwyRuler

<!-- ##### SECTION Short_Description ##### -->
Base class for #GwyHRuler and #GwyVRuler

<!-- ##### SECTION Long_Description ##### -->
<para>
#GwyRuler is a ruler similar to #GtkRuler, but it is more suited for
a scientific application.  It is scale-independent and thus has no arbitrary
limits on the ranges or interpretation of displayed values.  It can display
units on the ruler (this can be controlled with
gwy_ruler_set_units_placement()) and cooperates with #GwySIUnit (see
gwy_ruler_set_units()).  It also better follows Gtk+ theme than #GtkRuler.
</para>

<!-- ##### SECTION See_Also ##### -->
<para>
#GwyVRuler, #GwyHRuler, #GwySIUnit.
</para>

